en_9227284_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – A survey had revealed that 30% of those with diabetes are diagnosed with eye-related conditions namely diabetic retinopathy.
en_9227284_1	Consultant eye surgeon of the National Eye Hospital, Dr Kapila Banduthilaka noted that diabetes has caused the rapid increase of the eye conditions in Sri Lanka.
en_9227284_2	The survey further revealed that 10% of diabetes patients have lost their eyesight partially while 1%-4% have lost their sight completely.
en_9227284_3	Dr Kapila Banduthilaka added that measures can be taken to prevent eye diseases caused by diabetes.
